# Environment Variables Template

Copy this content into a `.env.local` file in your Next.js project root directory.

```
# ============================
# RAZORPAY CONFIGURATION
# ============================
# Get these from: https://dashboard.razorpay.com/settings/api-keys

NEXT_PUBLIC_RAZORPAY_KEY_ID=rzp_live_xxxxxxxxxxxxx

RAZORPAY_KEY_SECRET=your_razorpay_key_secret_here_keep_it_secret

# ============================
# FIREBASE CONFIGURATION
# ============================
# Get these from Firebase Console → Project Settings → Service Accounts

FIREBASE_PROJECT_ID=your-project-id

FIREBASE_CLIENT_EMAIL=firebase-adminsdk-xxxxx@your-project-id.iam.gserviceaccount.com

FIREBASE_PRIVATE_KEY="-----BEGIN RSA PRIVATE KEY-----\nMIIEpAIBAAKCAQEA...\n-----END RSA PRIVATE KEY-----\n"

FIREBASE_DATABASE_URL=https://your-project-id.firebaseio.com

# ============================
# APPLICATION CONFIGURATION
# ============================

NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE=http://localhost:3000

# For production (Vercel):
# NEXT_PUBLIC_API_BASE=https://your-app.vercel.app

# ============================
# DEVELOPMENT FLAGS
# ============================

NODE_ENV=development
```

## ⚠️ IMPORTANT NOTES

1. **Never commit `.env.local`** to GitHub - add to `.gitignore`
2. **FIREBASE_PRIVATE_KEY**: Keep line breaks as `\n` in the string
3. **RAZORPAY_KEY_SECRET**: This is sensitive - never share publicly
4. **NEXT_PUBLIC_* variables**: These are exposed to browser (use non-sensitive data)

## Getting Your Keys

### Razorpay
1. https://dashboard.razorpay.com
2. Settings → API Keys
3. Copy the live/test Key ID and Secret

### Firebase
1. https://console.firebase.google.com
2. Project Settings → Service Accounts tab
3. Click "Generate New Private Key"
4. Use values from downloaded JSON file

